{
  "texts": [
    "As a use case we have generated narratives describing cancer patients.",
    "We have selected this disease due to its inherent complexity in the description not only of the disease but also its anatomical description and estimation of its severity.Despite we generated several narratives with an acceptable structure, and that the validation with real narratives delivered an acceptable precision (0.85 for models trained with Q2 prompts), we have observed that this method still has several serious limitations: a.",
    "Simplistic data: data synthetization is of course not the right solution since it tends to generate more or less regular texts and does not contain all the nuances of real narratives, considering that we have adjusted the text generation temperature. b.",
    "Missing details: real medical narratives are composed using more precise descriptions, for instance considering biomarkers and symptoms levels.",
    "Furthermore, some of the synthetized narratives have a very naïve style, which does not reflect the level of professional competence required in the medical feld."
  ]
}